{
  "stem": "3631.3",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I usually worked for the Schutzhaftlagerfuhrer.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The-- the ghetto, the camp was-- had different subdivisions, like-- like-- like a [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One was a Schutzhaftlagerfuhrer, actually, [INAUDIBLE] protective custody-- custody camp, but it was not for our protection.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was the-- the sleeping quarters of the-- of the people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And another area were-- were the workshops, where the work was, and another area, where the administration buildings were, and the other areas where the Germans lived.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So I was in cha-- I worked with the man, whoever he was at that time, who was in charge.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was usually a cap-- lieutenant or a first lieutenant who-- who was in charge, and I worked in his office.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, you had to be on their [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- you could-- you were not allowed to know everything, yet I had to know everything.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That's why I learned to-- to read letters upside down, or-- or read carbon papers where you see-- because if they couldn't find anything, they come to you.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was slapped a few times.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember one incident where we had a fairly decent man there, his name of Grimm, G-R-I-M-M.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I took the dictation.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I stood in front of his desk, or I sat in front of his desk, and I fell asleep with a pencil in my hand.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Now with another man, that would have been the end, but he-- and I sat at-- we had-- we had a big problem with-- with bugs and fleas, bedbugs and fleas.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When you have hundreds of bedbugs at night, you don't sleep.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And if you're undernourished and you don't have enough food.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I told him that I couldn't sleep at night, I'm busy with bedbugs.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
